Leroy J. Toppins went missing on Friday night while playing with siblings in the front yard of his family 's home in Washington Court House , Ohio .
More than 100 locals joined a search for the toddler that the boy 's body was found in a pond at an old stone quarry , a short distance from where he was last seen .
Police say they have no reason to consider the death of Leroy suspicious , believing he wandered off by himself .